RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 56. Maiden Claiming Purse 10000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000, if for $7,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OUT OF STARS prompted PERCY'S SIS from along the outside, took the lead from that one leaving the eighth pole and gradually drew clear. PERCY'S SIS saved ground setting the pace, responded when asked but was unable to stay with the winner late while continuing on gamely for the place. GOIN' COASTAL was close up from the start while racing along the inside, angled out nearing the eighth pole to be wide and finished well in a steady effort. BABY MARTINI was prominent early racing between horses, dropped back slightly nearing the turn, came five-wide into the stretch but lacked a rally.. FLYING SYLVIA was forwardly placed for a half mile while three-wide but came up empty during the drive.

ENTRY.NAME: Goin' Coastal
ENTRY.COMMENT: close up, saved ground, angled out 1/8, steady effort

ENTRY.NAME: Percy's Sis
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pace, saved ground, responded, held gamely

ENTRY.NAME: Baby Martini
ENTRY.COMMENT: prominent early, dropped back 1/2, 5-wide entering, lacked rally

ENTRY.NAME: Out of Stars
ENTRY.COMMENT: prompted pace 2-wide, led leaving 1/8, drew clear

RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 75. Claiming Purse 8500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE MAY 6, 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $2,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HEAT SEEKING LETA saved ground while being unhurried, angled out two-wide to come between horses leaving the three-sixteenths pole, took command inside the eighth pole and quickly drew clear. WARREN'S MEMORABLE dropped back early, rallied five-wide into the stretch and finished full of run. BELLS AND WHISTLES vied with CONFIDENCE BUILDER from along the inside, shook that one off leaving the three-sixteenths pole, but was unable to resist the top two late. ROLINGA saved ground stalking the pace, angled out to come four-wide into the stretch but lacked a rally. CONFIDENCE BUILDER vied for the lead from along the outside to the stretch, drifted out slightly nearing the three-sixteenths pole and tired.

ENTRY.NAME: Heat Seeking Leta
ENTRY.COMMENT: unhurried, saved ground, angled out, split rivals, drew clear

ENTRY.NAME: Warren's Memorable
ENTRY.COMMENT: dropped back, 5-wide entering, full of run

ENTRY.NAME: Confidence Builder
ENTRY.OWNER: White Diamond Syndicate Crandall Gary and Breyer Tom

RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 8000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 6, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $2,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PURPLE NIGHT vied with SHESRSECRETWEAPON for the lead from along the inside, shook that one off entering the stretch and maintained a safe advantage. MIST OONA B saved ground while being allowed to settle, angled out two-wide to offer a bid leaving the quarter pole, could not reach the winner but finished strongly for the place. SHESRSECRETWEAPON vied for the lead from along the outside, drifted out slightly at the quarter pole and held on fairly well for show. GUNNHILD was reserved off the early pace, angled out to be four-wide entering the stretch but lacked a rally. DRINKUP BUTTERCUP was rank to place for the opening quarter pole while racing along the inside, dropped back to get to the outside, raced five-wide from that point and failed to menace.

ENTRY.COMMENT: rank opening 1/4, angled out 5-wide, no menace

RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 4 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 77. Claiming Purse 9500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COASTARANDO was forwardly placed while racing two-wide, moved up to join DANIEELE'S SECRET entering the stretch, took the lead nearing the eighth pole and gradually increased her advantage. SHEMAKESCENTS was close up early racing along the inside, checked nearing the seven-sixteenths pole in traffic, dropped back, then moved forward again along the inside nearing the stretch, angled out 2-wide nearing the eighth pole and finished strongly. DANIELLE'S SECRET saved ground setting the pace into the stretch and weakened when headed. RODEO ROSE was allowed to settle, moved up four-wide nearing the quarter pole and went evenly late. SPANISH CHANNEL reserved off the early pace, moved up five-wide nearing the quarter pole but lacked a rally. DONTFORGETHESUGAR was unhurried early, came six-wide into the stretch and failed to seriously threaten.

ENTRY.NAME: Shemakescents
ENTRY.COMMENT: closed up inside, checked 7/16, inside rally, strong finished

ENTRY.NAME: Coastarando
ENTRY.COMMENT: forwardly placed, 2-wide, led near 1/8, increased advantage

ENTRY.NAME: Danielle's Secret
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pace, saved ground, weakened late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 5 1M Dirt CR: 85. Claiming Purse 18000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000, if for $12,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden Races, Claiming Races And Starters Races For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HOLLYWOOD MISTRESS bobbled at the start, then was reserved off the pace, moved up three-wide nearing the quarter pole, brushed with SHERILINDA leaving the three-sixteenths pole, took the lead nearing the eighth pole and won drawing clear. SHERILINDA prompted BRILLIANT BIRD while racing two-wide, came out slightly to brush with the winner leaving the three-sixteenths pole and finished strongly for second. BRILLIANT BIRD saved ground setting the pace, was unable to stay with the top two late but held on fairly well for third. IN THE RED was close up early racing along the inside, checked nearing the three-quarter pole lacking room, dropped back slightly while continuing to save ground, angled out 1/8, mild rally. EMERALD SEA was allowed to settled, came three-wide into the stretch but lacked a rally. MS LYNN was unhurried while saving ground and failed to menace.

ENTRY.NAME: In the Red
ENTRY.COMMENT: close up early, checked 3/4, saved ground, mild rally

ENTRY.NAME: Hollywood Mistress
ENTRY.OWNER: BDW Racing LLC and Sudo Shawn
ENTRY.COMMENT: bobbled start, reserved, 3-wide 1/4, brushed 3/16, drew clear

ENTRY.NAME: Sherilinda
ENTRY.COMMENT: prompted 2-wide, came out brushed 3/16, strong finish

RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 6 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 76. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000, if for $12,500, allowed 3 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NAPOLETANO was reserved off the pace while saving ground, angled out to be three-wide entering, then angled in nearing the eighth pole to split rivals and finished fast to be up in the final sixteenth. ICE TOWER settled in the middle of the pack, split rivals nearing the three-eighths pole while moving forward, came three-wide into the stretch, gained a slight lead during the drive but couldn't quite resist the winner. TIME 'ER TOO was allowed to settle, rallied five-wide the final quarter and finished strongly. REIGN OF SPEED prompted the pace while racing two-wide, came four-wide into the stretch and finished well in a steady effort. SARGENT KLINE saved ground while being unhurried, came three-wide into the stretch and gained his best stride too late. MISTER MAFIOSO vied for the lead to the stretch while two-wide and weakened. ICE NEEDS WHISKEY vied for the early lead from along the inside and gave way after three furlongs. HOWDOYALIKEMENOW dropped back while saving ground and failed to threaten. CONTEJAS gave way after showing brief speed from between horses.

ENTRY.COMMENT: reserved, 3-wide entering, angled in, split rivals, up final 1/16

RACE.FOOTNOTES: LADY BRETT saved ground setting the pace in hand and maintained a safe advantage. MISS ACCELERATE saved ground chasing the winner and was gaining slightly late. I AM YOURS was unhurried early, rallied five-wide into the stretch and finished full of run. SETTLER'S COVE was forwardly placed while racing three-wide but lacked the needed late response. AWESOME DAZE dropped back early, came four-wide into the stretch and failed to seriously threaten. DAREDEVIL PRINCESS was prominently placed to the stretch while two-wide and tired. PHOENICIAN MAGIC gave way after showing brief early speed.

ENTRY.COMMENT: set pace in hand, saved ground, maintained safe advantage
